node.text:
A sensorially inquisitive journey is set into motion at AZULIK by nothing more than a sight of nature coexisting dynamically with the everyday experience of life. Whole lives are influenced by the simplest and most unexamined images of happiness-- where people are reconnected with nature, art, and ancestry. Co-create to Re-connect with us!

@contentcreator.team @contentcreator.re

node.text:
It’s a journey that constantly transforms and which we are always rediscovering. The  electo-acoustic sounds of Hermano Bosque, a project born in Tulum, is a voyage where real-time creation and live instruments compose an organic experience to make us reconnect with one another through music.

#Azulik #azuliktulum #azuliksounds #InBetween

node.text:
Greetings from SFER IK at UH MAY, a museion that houses temporary exhibitions in an im/permanent living shelter for the arts. Settled amid the jungle’s tree columns, SFER IK bridges the local and the universal, by uniting craftsmen and contemporary artists in a close-knit community, whose sole purpose is to craft new gateways to experience art as you have never before. Plan your visit through the link in our bio.
.
.
.
.
.
#art #gallery #contemporary #ancient #jungle #jointhetribe #architecture #slowliving #design #experience #reconnect #drone #dronevideo #Azulik #UhMay #SferIk

@tulumensemble is an extraordinary project that blends synthetic moods and native instruments to create a fusion of electronic music and earthy soundscapes. Their vision is to transport their listeners to alternate states of consciousness. We were thrilled to have them in our In Between sessions here at AZULIK. .
.
.
.
.

@elilight9, joined us for our immersive happening, In between. Born in Colombia, Eli Light has devoted her life to create music that is imbibed with ancestrality and inspires deep-rootedness to the present. As an outstanding artist in the electronic music scene, she seeks to transport listeners to another spiritual dimension, where different cultures and primeval sounds converge. We were infused with energy thanks to her talent in weaving the perfect soundscape. .
.
.
.
.
.
#AZULIK #AZULIKTulum #AZULIKsounds #Tulum #Inbetween  #art #abovethetrees #tseenja

TRECE VEINTE (13:20) is the natural frequency of time in which life operates in a harmonic and synchronized way. Based on this ideology, musicians Victor Ortiz and Mario Zetter started experimenting with sounds and ancestral instruments to channel pre-Hispanic heritage into new harmonies and vibrations.
.
.
#AZULIK #AZULIKSounds #InBetween #TseenJa #Sunset #Tulum

node.text:
In Between - Ottmann. Arabic, African, Berber and Andalusian sounds give life to the music of Ottmann, Paris-based Moroccan DJ and founder of Medina Party. His country’s rich history has inspired a rhythm that fuses ethnic music with percussions that transport us to his corner of the world, a heritage he has come to share with the tribe during Tulum’s magical sunsets. .
.
#Azulik #AzulikSounds #InBetween  #Tulum #Tulumevents

node.text:
Born in Caracas, Venezuela, Giorgio Maulini has always been passionate about music. He discovered his gift for music production at 16 when he left for Spain, and a few years later he connected with the Underground Music Movement in Copenhagen. Reading the dancefloor and feeding off the atmosphere in the club, he taps into a wealth of musical knowledge to deliver sets full of energy, individuality and spontaneity, which he brought to the terrace of AZULIK o light up the sunset.
🎵 @giorgiomau .
.

#AZULIK #AZULIKTulum #Tulum #inbetween #AZULIKsounds #art #abovethetrees #tseenja
